 <purpose>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for elemental
topology. This part of ISO 10303 provides for the definition of the overall
class of topological elements, and includes  detailed definitions of some basic 
topological representation items. This module contains pure topology with no geometric associations.
 <!-- 2nd edition changes -->
        <p>
                The second edition of this part of ISO 10303 incorporates the modifications to the first edition listed below.  
        </p>
 <p> The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been added:
  </p>
  
 <ul>
 <li> Connected_edge_set;       </li>
 <li> Connected_face_set;       </li>
 <li> Edge;     </li>
 <li> Edge_loop         </li>
 <li> Face;     </li>
 <li> Face_bound;       </li>
 <li> Face_outer_bound;         </li>
 <li> Loop; </li>
 <li> Oriented_edge; </li>
 <li> Path; </li>
 <li> Vertex; </li>
 <li> Vertex_loop. </li>
 </ul>
 In addition the module now contains functions used to validate some of the elements.
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>
     the definition of the overall class of topological elements; 
   </li>
 <li>
      the definition of the basic topological constructs vertex, edge and face; 
         </li>
 <li>
      connected sets of basic topological elements; 
   </li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     any topological element with explicitly defined geometry. 
   </li>
 </outscope>
